2026-05-27 11:08:24,892 [openai._base_client] DEBUG: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'headers': {'X-Stainless-Helper-Method': 'chat.completions.parse'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-8e553132-6c2c-4076-a8a3-149af515a187', 'post_parser': <function Completions.parse.<locals>.parser at 0x10dff5800>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'You are an accounts receivable assistant parsing an inbound client reply.\n\nTODAY\'S DATE: 2026-05-27\n\nCLIENT NAME: Orion Dynamics\n\nINCOMING EMAIL TEXT:\nHi, sorry for the delay. I can get this paid by next Friday. We\'ve had some internal approvals holding things up but it\'s all sorted now. Apologies again.\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\n1. Determine the intent of this email. Choose exactly one of:\n   - "promise_to_pay": the client explicitly commits to paying by a specific date\n   - "dispute": the client is contesting the invoice amount or charges\n   - "ignore": the client is not engaging meaningfully\n   - "paid": the client claims they have already paid\n   - "other": anything else\n\n2. If the intent is "promise_to_pay", extract the payment promise date.\n   - If the date is expressed as a relative term (e.g. "next Friday", "end of next week",\n     "by Thursday"), resolve it to an absolute date in YYYY-MM-DD format using\n     TODAY\'S DATE (2026-05-27) as the reference point.\n   - If no specific date is mentioned, set promise_date to null.\n\n3. Write a brief parsed_summary (1-2 sentences) describing the client\'s message\n   and its implications for the outstanding invoice.\n\nReturn your result in the requested JSON structure.\n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'json_schema': {'schema': {'properties': {'intent': {'enum': ['promise_to_pay', 'dispute', 'ignore', 'paid', 'other'], 'title': 'Intent', 'type': 'string'}, 'promise_date': {'anyOf': [{'type': 'string'}, {'type': 'null'}], 'title': 'Promise Date'}, 'parsed_summary': {'title': 'Parsed Summary', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['intent', 'promise_date', 'parsed_summary'], 'title': 'ParsedReply', 'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False}, 'name': 'ParsedReply', 'strict': True}}, 'stream': False}}
