2026-05-27 14:14:40,046 [openai._base_client] DEBUG: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'headers': {'X-Stainless-Helper-Method': 'chat.completions.parse'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-ac4dcf30-ed08-42c1-b9c8-56d3e4cc0859', 'post_parser': <function Completions.parse.<locals>.parser at 0x11a98f950>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'You are a senior finance manager writing a formal dispute\nletter to a vendor on behalf of your company.\n\nINVOICE DETAILS:\n  Invoice Number : INV-2024-0847\n  Vendor Name    : ACME CORP\n  Billing Contact: billing@acmecorp.com\n  Invoice Date   : 2024-11-04\n  Total Billed   : USD 3127.50\n\nDISCREPANCIES FOUND:\n  - Field: line_items[0].unit_price\n    Expected: 0.012 or less per call\n    Actual: 0.019 per call\n    Severity: error\n    Detail: Unit price for API calls exceeds the contract\'s ceiling rate of $0.012 per call.\n  - Field: line_items[2].description\n    Expected: Not billed\n    Actual: Platform Maintenance Fee\n    Severity: error\n    Detail: Platform Maintenance Fee is not a permitted billing category under the contract.\n  - Field: line_items[3].description\n    Expected: Permitted list item or authorized via SOW\n    Actual: Data Export Service\n    Severity: warning\n    Detail: Data Export Service is not explicitly listed as a permitted billing category.\n  - Field: tax\n    Expected: consistent with applicable tax rate or contract\n    Actual: 0.0\n    Severity: warning\n    Detail: No tax was applied, which may not align with potential state or contract tax obligations.\n\nPAYMENT STATUS:\nIMPORTANT: This invoice has ALREADY BEEN PAID via auto-pay. The tone must be urgent. Demand an immediate refund of the overcharged amount.\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\nWrite a professional, firm dispute letter that:\n1. Opens with a clear statement of the dispute and the invoice reference.\n2. Provides a line-by-line breakdown of each overcharge with exact dollar\n   amounts (expected vs. actual).\n3. Cites the specific contract clause, section, or pricing term that is\n   violated for each item.\n4. Requests a credit memo or full refund of the overcharged amount within\n   14 business days.\n5. If already_paid is True: lead with urgency — state that payment was\n   processed in error and demand immediate refund.\n6. Closes with a professional escalation warning (e.g., escalation to legal\n   or withholding of future payments) if the matter is not resolved within\n   the stated timeframe.\n\nFill all fields of the DisputeEmail model:\n  - recipient: the billing contact email (use billing@acmecorp.com\n    or "billing@acmecorp.com" if blank)\n  - subject: concise subject line referencing invoice number and dispute\n  - body: the complete letter text\n  - invoice_number: INV-2024-0847\n  - urgent_flag: true if already_paid is True or any flag has severity "error",\n    otherwise false\n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'json_schema': {'schema': {'properties': {'recipient': {'title': 'Recipient', 'type': 'string'}, 'subject': {'title': 'Subject', 'type': 'string'}, 'body': {'title': 'Body', 'type': 'string'}, 'invoice_number': {'title': 'Invoice Number', 'type': 'string'}, 'urgent_flag': {'default': False, 'title': 'Urgent Flag', 'type': 'boolean'}}, 'required': ['recipient', 'subject', 'body', 'invoice_number', 'urgent_flag'], 'title': 'DisputeEmail', 'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False}, 'name': 'DisputeEmail', 'strict': True}}, 'stream': False}}
