2026-05-27 14:15:02,541 [openai._base_client] DEBUG: Request options: {'method': 'post', 'url': '/chat/completions', 'headers': {'X-Stainless-Helper-Method': 'chat.completions.parse'}, 'files': None, 'idempotency_key': 'stainless-python-retry-dc52c5ee-1117-48d6-ae65-db3c9436151d', 'post_parser': <function Completions.parse.<locals>.parser at 0x11aa4cbf0>, 'security': {'bearer_auth': True}, 'content': None, 'json_data': {'messages': [{'role': 'user', 'content': 'You are an accounts receivable specialist drafting a collections email on behalf of LedgerShield Inc.\n\nCLIENT DETAILS:\n  Client Name   : Meridian Group\n  Amount Due    : $28,500.00 USD\n  Days Overdue  : 67 days\n  Contact Email : cfo@meridiangroup.com\n\nESCALATION TIER: FINAL_DEMAND\nTONE INSTRUCTIONS: Use a severe and urgent tone. State plainly that the account will be referred to a third-party collections agency within 5 business days if the outstanding balance is not paid in full. This is the final communication before external escalation.\n\nPRIOR EMAIL HISTORY (oldest first):\n  Date: 2026-02-19\n  From: ar@ledgershield.com\n  To: cfo@meridiangroup.com\n  Subject: Invoice AR-1072 – $28,500.00 Due March 21, 2026 – LedgerShield Inc.\n  Body:\nHi Patricia,\n\nPlease find Invoice AR-1072 attached for your review and processing.\n\n  Invoice Number : AR-1072\n  Invoice Date   : February 19, 2026\n  Amount Due     : $28,500.00\n  Payment Due    : March 21, 2026\n  Payment Terms  : Net-30\n\nThis invoice covers the annual LedgerShield Enterprise license renewal and the Q4 2025 professional services engagement (implementation phase 2) as documented in Change Order #3 to your Master Service Agreement.\n\nGiven the size of this invoice, I wanted to flag it early so your AP team has sufficient lead time. Please don\'t hesitate to reach out if you need a W-9, updated banking details, or any documentation your finance team requires.\n\nThank you for the continued partnership, Patricia. We\'re excited to support Meridian Group\'s growth this year.\n\nBest regards,\nSophia Reeves\nAccounts Receivable | LedgerShield Inc.\nar@ledgershield.com | +1 (415) 882-3300\n\n---\n\n  Date: 2026-05-06\n  From: cfo@meridiangroup.com\n  To: ar@ledgershield.com\n  Subject: Re: Invoice AR-1072 – $28,500.00 Due March 21, 2026 – LedgerShield Inc.\n  Body:\nSophia,\n\nMy apologies – this one has slipped through the cracks longer than it should have. I take full responsibility.\n\nWe have been in the middle of a significant restructuring of our finance function and a number of payables got held up in the transition. Invoice AR-1072 is approved on our side and is sitting in the payment queue.\n\nI fully expect this to be settled by end of April. You have my word on it.\n\nSorry again for the delay and thank you for your patience.\n\nPatricia Owens\nChief Financial Officer | Meridian Group\ncfo@meridiangroup.com | +1 (312) 774-0900\n\n---\n\n  Date: 2026-05-12\n  From: ar@ledgershield.com\n  To: cfo@meridiangroup.com\n  Subject: Re: Invoice AR-1072 – Missed Payment Commitment – Urgent Follow-Up\n  Body:\nHi Patricia,\n\nThank you for your message on May 6. We appreciated the transparency regarding your internal restructuring and accepted your commitment to settle Invoice AR-1072 by the end of April.\n\nUnfortunately, as of today, May 12, 2026, payment has not been received. Invoice AR-1072 for $28,500.00 is now 52 days past its original due date of March 21, 2026.\n\nThis balance is now significantly overdue and we are unable to defer further action without a concrete resolution. We are requesting:\n\n  1. Immediate wire transfer of the full amount, OR\n  2. A written payment plan with specific dates and partial amounts, confirmed by reply to this email no later than May 15, 2026.\n\nFailure to respond by May 15 will require us to escalate this matter to our collections team and, if necessary, engage legal counsel as permitted under our service agreement.\n\nPatricia, we have valued this relationship and want to find a way forward that works for both organizations. Please respond urgently so we can avoid that path.\n\nRegards,\nSophia Reeves\nAccounts Receivable | LedgerShield Inc.\nar@ledgershield.com | +1 (415) 882-3300\n\nCC: Daniel Park, VP Finance – dpark@ledgershield.com\n\nINSTRUCTIONS:\nDraft a collections email appropriate for the escalation tier. The email must:\n1. Open with a clear, direct reference to the outstanding invoice and amount.\n2. Reference prior communications where relevant.\n3. State a specific payment deadline (within 7 days).\n4. Apply the tone described above without deviation.\n5. Include a professional sign-off from the LedgerShield AR team.\n\nFill all fields of the CollectionsEmail model:\n  - recipient: the client\'s billing contact email (cfo@meridiangroup.com)\n  - client_name: exactly "Meridian Group"\n  - subject: a concise subject line referencing the overdue balance\n  - body: the complete email body text\n  - escalation_tier: exactly "final_demand"\n'}], 'model': 'gpt-4o-mini', 'response_format': {'type': 'json_schema', 'json_schema': {'schema': {'properties': {'recipient': {'title': 'Recipient', 'type': 'string'}, 'client_name': {'title': 'Client Name', 'type': 'string'}, 'subject': {'title': 'Subject', 'type': 'string'}, 'body': {'title': 'Body', 'type': 'string'}, 'escalation_tier': {'enum': ['firm_reminder', 'legal_notice', 'final_demand'], 'title': 'Escalation Tier', 'type': 'string'}}, 'required': ['recipient', 'client_name', 'subject', 'body', 'escalation_tier'], 'title': 'CollectionsEmail', 'type': 'object', 'additionalProperties': False}, 'name': 'CollectionsEmail', 'strict': True}}, 'stream': False}}
